JFK assassination
theories discussed

By Cameron Harvey
staff Writer

The Warren Commission’s findings in the
Kennedy assassination were completely inaccurate,
according to forensicsspecialist Dr. Cyril Wecht.

“Just begin to read and study. Your mind will not
let you believe the Warren Commission if you have
a drop of intelligence,” Wechttold the standing
roomonly audience last night.

Sponsored by the University Democrats, Wecht
vacillated between a whisper and a roar describing

‘his theories to debunk not only the Warren

Commission"s report, but Gerald Posner’s new
book, Case Closed., which deals with JFK’s assassi-
nation.

According to Wecht, 75 to 80 percent of the
American public rejects the Warren Commission's
findings with this number steadily rising.

Posner’s credibility is questionable, according to
Wecht.

“Posner comes across as a radiologist,_a comput-
er specialist, a ballistics expert and a forensics spe-
cialist .. all this from a Wall Street lawyer with no
medical lawsuit experience of any kind,” Wecht
said.

Of the actual examination by 32 medical special-
ists at the time of Kennedy’s assassination, the
Warren Commission says that, “all 32 erred that
night [in the location of the would upon Kennedy’s
head]. What is the probability of that,” Wecht said.

Wecht questioned the audience.

Why would Lee Harvey Ozwald try to assassinate '

Kennedy from the vantage point at which
he allegedly did when trees were blocking the
shot? _

Wecht said that if Ozwald had attempted the shot
minutes before it would have been “Duck Soup,” as
there were no trees in his line of fire.

As to why the government would cover-up the

‘fact that more than one assassin might have acted,

Wecht mentioned that by definition Judicial Codes

define an illegal action by more than one person as‘

a conspiracy. By naming Lee Harvey O/zwald the
lone assassin, the government was saved the extra
task of trying to track down another assassin after
Ozwald’s assassination, Wecht said.

“lTl1e Warren Commission] cannot move from the
single—bullet theory because then it is finished,”
Wecht said.

