Casey receives good report at check-up

By Brian Lehew
For The Pitt News

Doctors at the University of
Pittsburgh Medical Center reported
Gov. Robert P. Casey's condition
as “very good” following a rou-

tine checkup Tuesday — three
months after his double heart—liver
transplant.

The governor’s test results showed
his new heart had normal blood flow

and neither organ showed any signs
of rejection.

According to UPMC spokesperson.

Jane Duffield, doctors report-
ed Casey’s test results as encourag-
ing.

Doctors lowered Casey’s dosage
of the experimental drug FKSO6, used
to prevent rejection of the new
organs. Casey was placed on the
drug following his dual transplant in
June to enhance his chances of sur-

vival.

Since a previous heart biopsy
showed no signs of rejection, the
governor was able‘ to skip the biopsy
scheduled for this visit.

. The governor left Presbyterian
University Hospital at 12:50 pm. yes-
terday. He will return to UPMC in
two weeks for another checkup and
will receive another biopsy at that
time.

